o the Oracle<br>
Oracle gives you Miragul's Phylactery(sp), which contains Miragul's soul.<br>
Give Miragul his soul, he spawns alive. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulannellavelglarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lannella Velglarn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/hottopic.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/01 3:08:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NOT the book of scale!</span><hr size=1> Thing about the Oasis firepot is, even if it was 'implied' by the GM I spoke to (who *only* asked if I'd looked there), would evil characters not be killed by the spectres?  If a Troll SK popped in, wouldn't they still attack?  Specs, after all, are factionless and not subject to kissing up (contrast the pets in QCat SK area). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uladassindarin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ladas Sindarin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/01 4:04:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NOT the book of scale!</span><hr size=1> And how is that different from the Ice Bones in the broken portal room in Everfrost?  Or to a  lesser extent, the Shadowmen you ambush you at the Innothule Swamp portal? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulannellavelglarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lannella Velglarn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/hottopic.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/01 9:42:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NOT the book of scale!</span><hr size=1> I wouldn't really know but, from what I've heard and am now reminded of, you may have a valid point.  Maybe, IF the Oasis firepot is an exit, its intent is for the use of high level (spec surviving) players.<br>
<br>
Ladas, can you elaborate on the 'broken portal room' in Everfrost?  This sounds like the room I'm looking to check out but I want to be sure.  Has it ever (to any player's knowledge) been used?  If so, from where? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uimmortalis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Immortalis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/28/01 11:05:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NOT the book of scale!</span><hr size=1> I studied this a long time ago...and have visited the portal room in the underground caves many times.  It has never worked since release, however I dont know what purpose it served in beta. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubloodshard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bloodshard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/28/01 6:17:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Has anyone tried using the Soul Trap box</span><hr size=1> To see if it's a key?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=662">everquest.allakhazam.com/...?quest=662</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
I may be way off base but it ties to Miragul. And it is the only quests that actual raises faction with that nasty lich by the one teleporter. Or perhaps a step towards they key?<br>
<br>
Tough quest though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulannellavelglarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lannella Velglarn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/hottopic.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/29/01 3:06:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Has anyone tried using the Soul Trap box</span><hr size=1> Very tough quest.<br>
<br>
Well, I went in the Lair tonight and got some answers for myself.<br>
1) Lich is blue to me at 47 -- therefore, not 53 like I'd heard<br>
2) Lich does not SeeInvis (was stationary, hidden only and indiff)<br>
3) Lich is definitely Not on Heretic faction (I'm dubious to them, KoS to Lich)<br>
4) Teleporter is indeed locked up.  It ports you about 3 metres from its entrance.<br>
5) Teleporter is *not* a firepot but more of a chamber (just neat to know)<br>
6) The necro Sulon is also not on Heretic faction.<br>
<br>
Now that I've done that, I'm at a loss for where to look next.   Aaargh. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urediofqeynos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Redi of Qeynos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/29/01 5:20:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: evil porters</span><hr size=1> Just to reply to your first post - wouldn't darky wizzies be evil porters? (&quot;No evil 'porters in game,&quot; you said).<br>
<br>
I've seen locked firepot discussion elsewhere... I know one place (albeit extraordinarily unreliable) is at the everlore page. IIRC, there's a quest topic &quot;Locket Firepit teleporter to lesser fay&quot; or some such. You may want to mine that for some data.<br>
<br>
GL <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
-Redi <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulannellavelglarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lannella Velglarn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/hottopic.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/29/01 8:43:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: evil porters</span><hr size=1> I'd corrected myself elsewhere about the lack of evil porters - must've been a different board.  Still, the numbers of DE wizards is miniscule compared to the other combinations of Porters, wouldn't you say? One race+class vs. a few races+2 classes.<br>
<br>
So far, I've only found this:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  In a few places around the world (Neriak, Qeynos, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Crushbone</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->) there are firepots, much like the ones in TD. I was told that those tents had Teir'Dal symbols all over them, and I believe that the firepots have been activated... if not then they soon will be. From what I can tell the firepots are one way and the ending spot for one in Neriak is those 2 tents. I assume <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> the one in Crushbone</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is the way back to Neriak as we all know there is an Alliance. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I'll take a spin through CB soon to try to verify any likely firepots.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukernn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kernn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/29/01 9:28:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> *Locked* Firepots - help</span><hr size=1> I could be wrong, but I remember hearing a long time ago that the spec tower in oasis was (was intended to be) the portal to Plane of Hate, like the portal to Fear.  But they removed it or didn't implement it so you would have to have a wizard to get you there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubenderlane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>benderlane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/29/01 3:01:06 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: *Locked* Firepots - help</span><hr size=1> I dont think this has anything to do with it, but has anyone ever figured out what the sphinxes in rathe are for?  I mean, with all the shpinx lore, etc, there has got to be someone who has been thinking about why an &quot;egyptian&quot; like beast would be living in (2 actually) a part of the world where there is no combine empire present.. <br>
<br>
I heard a rumor once that they were also related to a melee teleportation system that hadnt been discovered yet.. go figure. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uleechiii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leechiii</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/30/01 8:44:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: *Locked* Firepots - help</span><hr size=1> In regards to the tower setup with the symboling on top and firepot on the first floor.  In Lake of Rathe there is a similar setup in the tower on the island.  The roof has the pentagram with many symbols on it.  And as reported in similar findings it does not seem operable in any way. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulannellavelglarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lannella Velglarn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/hottopic.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/30/01 10:37:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: *Locked* Firepots - help</span><hr size=1> Based on the other 'identified' firepots, I would say that following those symbols would probably be a red herring.  Firepots so far, outside of TD, have all had the 'Evil Bunny' logo on them with little or no markings in the vicinity of them.  I'm open to the possibility that there may be other firepots but I'd expect them to match the artifacts within the TD room, to be honest.<br>
<br>
While the symbols may be worth researching, and *may* have a connection with the firepots somewhere down the line, I'd hate to see people trying to track info down on that angle alone.  I've seen threads elsewhere devoted to the symbols, though.<br>
<br>
One of the main things that I'm, personally, trying to be aware of are firepots that just seem *really* out of place.  Pots that are all by themselves; have 'evil' markings in a good town...etc. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utalnic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talnic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/1/01 11:38:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: *Locked* Firepots - help</span><hr size=1> The portal room on everfrost goes to "the Hive" a zone that has not been added yet, you can see it in the original book that came with EQ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulannellavelglarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lannella Velglarn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/hottopic.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/2/01 3:17:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: *Locked* Firepots - help</span><hr size=1> Just checking - by Everfrost, do you mean Halas.  And by &quot;The Hive&quot; do you mean &quot;The Nest&quot;?<br>
<br>
My original book has no map of Everfrost, but one of Halas and there is a reference to The Nest in the area in the water by the dock. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaroana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aroana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/4/01 6:04:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: *Locked* Firepots - help</span><hr size=1> Did you read the description of the new zone, Nexus on eqatlas?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The Nexus is the hub of all traffic coming to and leaving Luclin. Built ages ago by the Combine empire, it enabled them to travel to Luclin to escape their internal enemies. As Luclin moved further away from Norrath, however, the Nexus was unable to power transport back and forth between the two, and so became mostly unused except as a boring guard post. Now that Luclin has moved within range of Norrath again, the Nexus has come alive. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Makes me wonder if the firepots are activated now...<br>
<br>
<br>
map is <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqatlas.com/luclin/nexusmap.html">here.</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
TTFN~<br>
Aroana<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulannellavelglarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lannella Velglarn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/hottopic.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/5/01 9:17:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: *Locked* Firepots - help</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;Built ages ago by the Combine empire&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
That's the part that makes me doubtful.  Granted, Verant is not too thorough sometimes with their literature but, to be technical, the Firepots were made (as legend has it) by Miragul who was a *contemporary* of the Combine Empire, but not *of* the Combine Empire.<br>
It's still definitely worth checking out.  If the 'magicks of the Nexus' have re-enabled one set of portals, they may have likewise re-enabled another. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=3337.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3494.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3523.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=3337.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.threadControl?topicID=3337.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3337.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3337.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies">Training Studio<option value="thesafehousethebackroomsecretss